FBIS4-33128 "drlat106_t_94002" FBIS-LAT-94-106 Daily Report 1 Jun 1994 Venezuela President Reinstates Economic Guarantees President Reinstates Economic Guarantees PA0106175694 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1622 GMT 1 Jun 94 PA0106175694 Madrid EFE Spanish BFN [Text] Caracas, 1 Jun (EFE) -- Venezuelan President Rafael Caldera announced today that the economic guarantees established in the Venezuelan constitution have been reinstated. Caldera, who took over on 2 February, had suspended economic guarantees in order to implement several measures to reorganize the Venezuelan economy. The reestablishment of economic guarantees is one of the petitions that had been made by Venezuelan entrepreneurs to the Christian Democratic president.
